* TOUR NEWS AND VIEWS

ELS TAKES MERCEDES IN RECORD FASHION
Ernie Els carded a final-round 67 Sunday at the Mercedes Championships to
finish a PGA Tour-record 31-under par and collected $1 million for his
efforts. He stands atop the PGA Tour money list for the first time in his
career.

http://www.golfdigest.com/newsandtour/index.ssf?/newsandtour/2003mercedes.html

IMMELMAN WINS PLAYOFF IN SOUTH AFRICA
Trevor Immelman made a 6-inch birdie putt on the first playoff hole to
beat Tim Clark and won the South African Open on Sunday.

http://www.golfdigest.com/newsandtour/index.ssf?/newsandtour/2003southafricanairways.html

SIRAK: WELCOME BACK, ERNIE
Ernie Els has always had the game to be the chief rival for Tiger Woods,
but for some reason he has never risen to Tiger's level. But after a few
dormant years, Els seems poised to make a serious run at the world's best
player, writes Ron Sirak.

http://www.golfdigest.com/newsandtour/weekend/index.ssf?/newsandtour/weekend/20030113sirak.html

SOLTAU: FIRST TIMERS SOAK IT ALL IN
There were 18 first-time winners at Kapalua and as Mark Soltau writes,
they found that winning on the PGA Tour does have its privileges.

http://www.golfdigest.com/newsandtour/insider/index.ssf?/newsandtour/insider/20030109ropes.html

ROSAFORTE: STARTING OVER
With the PGA Tour season kicking off, Tim Rosaforte takes a step back to
put both life and golf in perspective thanks to a close friend who
overcame a debilitating injury to return to the course.

http://www.golfdigest.com/newsandtour/insider/index.ssf?/newsandtour/insider/20030107insider.html

MINNESOTA VIOLATION ALLEGATIONS DOUBTED 
Officials at the U of M will continue their investigation into the men's
golf team, but they have determined that the letter sent to them detailing
allegations of team members violating NCAA rules was not written by the
individual whose name appeared on it.

http://www.golfdigest.com/newsandtour/index.ssf?/newsandtour/20030108minnesota.html

FORMER CBS CEO WYMAN DEAD AT 73
Thomas H. Wyman, the former chairman and chief executive of CBS who
resigned last month from the Augusta National because of its all-male
membership, died Thursday at age 73.

http://www.golfdigest.com/newsandtour/index.ssf?/newsandtour/20030109wyman.html

GOLFDIGEST.COM's 2002 YEAR IN REVIEW
Tiger's run at the Grand Slam. Annika's 11 wins. Hootie's infamous letter
and ongoing battle with Martha. The ever-changing equipment landscape. Our
Year in Review compiles the best of the best from our three publications,
including original content, course reviews, instruction and much more!

http://www.golfdigest.com/features/index.ssf?/features/2002yearinreview.html

THIS WEEK ON TELEVISION
Ernie Els looks to continue his fine play at the Sony Open in Hawaii on
ESPN.

http://www.golfdigest.com/newsandtour/index.ssf?/newsandtour/thisweekontelevision.html
